ary."},"153":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-23","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#convert-one-unreliable-boundary-into-a-tuple","content":"Good tuple code usually starts at an edge: HTTP, files, subprocesses, validation, IPC, or user-provided data."},"154":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-24","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#fetch-json-with-a-real-deadline","content":"The timeout and parent `signal` are linked, so either one can stop the request."},"155":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-25","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#retry-only-the-noisy-dependency","content":"Avoid retrying the whole route handler. Validation, authorization, and side effects should not run again just because a remote service had a brief wobble."},"156":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-26","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#reuse-a-schedule-policy","content":"Schedules are useful when several call sites should share timing rules without sharing business logic."},"157":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-27","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#put-a-ceiling-on-a-shared-resource","content":"Use semaphores for \"only N at once.\" Use rate limiters for \"only N per time window.\""},"158":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-28","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#respect-an-api-quota","content":"Keeping the wait explicit makes quota pressure visible in code review."},"159":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-29","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/examples#hand-work-from-producers-to-workers","content":"Bound the queue when producers can outpace workers. Capacity is part of the user experience."},"160":{"id":"/docs/guides/examples-30","page_id":"/docs/guides/examples","tags":[],"typ